{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7425539b-d8a3-4185-a4cc-28893f332a8f","content":"Here's what you need. The key is four environment variables plus a volume for dump storage:\n\n**Environment variables:**\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump with heap |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/crashdumps/core.%p.%t` | Dump path (`%p`=PID, `%t`=timestamp) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Custom createdump location (required since it's not in the default SDK path) |\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/crashdumps/core.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crashdumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/crashdumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crashdumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- `DbgMiniDumpType=4` gives a full memory dump — use `2` (heap only) or `1` (normal/minimal) to reduce size.\n- The `emptyDir` with `sizeLimit` prevents a crash loop from filling the node's disk.\n- For NativeAOT, `DbgCreatedumpPath` is essential since there's no SDK to discover it automatically.\n- To persist dumps beyond pod lifetime, swap `emptyDir` for a `persistentVolumeClaim`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5bfe82d0-48e8-4174-a63e-0b9923f137ed","outputTokens":508,"requestId":"A0D2:2F657A:8FB412:B2018A:6A01367A"},"id":"9dc009f4-cd94-4af4-8660-2548d3330c64","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:53:09.853Z","parentId":"5e4dbeb6-df7d-469a-a11f-575934d9c3f2"}
